A Good Cassic. Little dated already, but still holds up well with it's design (colors x soundtrack).
Relatively short and mostly linear (which for ones might be a positive, while for the others - negative), with responsive fun controls.

Game rather for a single session, since there is not much to do after completing it.
Altho it's favorited by those who likes to speedrun (giving repetition reason).
Theoretically you can later unlock a Hard Mode... but with some random nonsenses, like unfair fights at the end, invisible walls and bugs... I would give a pass for it.

As for extra content, there is also a "DLC" - with maps purely focused on parkour.
Sadly no longer in a city, but still nice addition nonetheless.


[b]Positives[/b]:
- Concept Design;
- Soundtrack;
- Responsive Gameplay;
- Memorable levels;
- Reasonable Checkpoints;
- No "fillers."

[b]Negatives[/b]:
- Some annoying/unfair fights and bugs;
- Game narration/story could be a bit better;
- Unlocking certain things, like 120 fps or Windowed mode requires working with ini file or installing a mod;
- Steam version for whatever reason; lacks Polish dubbing (which was present around original PC release);
- Steam version to this day doesn't have achievements.


As for me, I would rate it 7.5/10

Must play for parkour lovers, since there is just but a few games like this to this day.
